  "name": "Spell Scroll (0 - Cantrip)",
  "type": "consumable",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written in a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class’s spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any &amp;Reference[material]{material} components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell’s normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p>\n<p>This scroll contains a cantrip. The spell's saving throw DC is 13 and attack bonus is +5.</p>\n</div>",
